The paper discusses recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the challenges faced by mobile devices, which suggests that the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category may also be relevant. The use of location data and processor speed also suggests that the Database (cs.DB) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories may be relevant. Finally, the paper may also touch on Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it discusses the relevance of data to the user.
